{
  "texts": [
    "It significantly improves the quantization accuracy of LLM's LoRA fine-tuning, facilitating practical deployment in resource-constrained scenarios.BiLLM [185] achieves extreme quantization, compressing the space occupied by each parameter to 1.1 bits.",
    "In the OPT model family, BiLLM achieves the most extreme post-training compression of LLMs with an average weight size of 1.1 bits, using 1 bit to approximate parameters in the network and 2 bits to represent some weights that significantly affect performance.",
    "On the Llama series of models, the BiLLM outperforms the full-precision OPT-66B model at 1.08 bits.",
    "In terms of efficiency, BiLLM can complete the binarization of a 7-billion LLM in half an hour on a single GPU.",
    "BiLLM employs a novel binary residual approximation strategy."
  ]
}